        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands.&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant and Importer&#44;<lb/>
                Purchaser of Real Estate&#44; &#40;Landed Property.&#41;<lb/>
                Residence&#44; 127 DARTMOUTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before sunset on<lb/> Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on<lb/> those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Adar 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> AM 5641<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear &#38; pious friend<lb/></p>
            <p>On behalf of my beloved wife daughter<lb/> &#38; son we have conjointly sent you a D&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> colour mantle clock &#38; bro&#91;&#63;&#93;ze&#44; as a joint<lb/> trifle in acknowledgement<sic></sic> of your long and<lb/> zealous work in the service of our Holy<lb/> and sacred faith believe me I love honor<lb/> and venerate every true Israelite but<lb/> such a bold and loving advocate in<lb/> these trying times such as you are nothing<lb/> is too much we owe you let me entreat<lb/> you not to send us any thanks believe<lb/> me it is only a reward from Heaven<lb/> I hope God blessings will ever be<lb/> your portion&#44; Regarding the thirty<lb/> thousand dollars indebtedness on your<lb/> Holy house we most sincerely pray<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>to God it may be our lot conjointly to<lb/> be very shortly in a position to<lb/> begin Late<sic></sic> that indebtedness&#44; all we<lb/> ask is you should fervently pray to<lb/> God to crown our efforts with<lb/> success.<lb/></p>
            <p>Wishing the Almighty God Holy<lb/> &#38; sacred Angels may guide you &#38;<lb/> all your family to success &#38; happiness<lb/> &#38; may your life be spared to see Zion<lb/> again in its Glory<lb/></p>
            <p>I am with due respect<lb/>
                Your&#39;s most fondly<lb/>
                &#38; faithfully<lb/>
                Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
        </body>
